gep.model

Class GeneElement<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gep.model.GeneElement<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The return type of the execution of this gene element
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GeneFunction, GeneTerminal

    public abstract class GeneElement<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class represents an element in a genes sequence. It is either a terminal (leaf) or a function (regular node) in the expression tree.
    Author:
    Johannes Wortmann
    See Also:

      • getArity

        public abstract int getArity()
        Returns the number of argument this element takes when executed. If it is a terminal this function is constant and has to return 0.
        Returns:
        The number of arguments for the encoded function.
